## PHASE 4: ANALYTICS & ACCESSIBILITY *(1 day)*

**Priority**: MEDIUM-HIGH - Can't optimize without data; accessibility improves engagement

### 4.1 Google Analytics 4 Setup
- Add GA4 code to all HTML pages (in `<head>` after meta tags):
  ```html
  <!-- Google Analytics -->
  <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-XXXXXXXXXX"></script>
  <script>
    window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
    function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
    gtag('js', new Date());
    gtag('config', 'G-XXXXXXXXXX');
  </script>
  ```
- Replace `G-XXXXXXXXXX` with actual GA4 property ID

### 4.2 Custom Event Tracking
- Track tool usage:
  ```javascript
  function trackToolUsage(toolName) {
    gtag('event', 'tool_usage', {
      'tool_name': toolName,
      'timestamp': new Date().toISOString()
    });
  }
  ```
- Track copy-to-clipboard clicks:
  ```javascript
  gtag('event', 'copy_clicked', {
    'tool_name': toolName
  });
  ```
- Track blog scroll depth:
  ```javascript
  document.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
    const scrollPercent = (window.scrollY / (document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight)) * 100;
    if (scrollPercent > 50) gtag('event', 'page_half_scrolled');
    if (scrollPercent > 90) gtag('event', 'page_almost_finished');
  });
  ```

### 4.3 Mobile Hamburger Menu
- Add to all pages header:
  ```html
  <button class="mobile-menu-toggle" id="mobileMenuToggle" aria-label="Toggle menu">
    <span></span><span></span><span></span>
  </button>
  ```
- Update CSS to show/hide nav on mobile:
  ```css
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-links { display: none; }
    .nav-links.active { display: block; }
    .mobile-menu-toggle { display: block; }
  }
  ```
- Add JavaScript:
  ```javascript
  document.getElementById('mobileMenuToggle')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.querySelector('.nav-links').classList.toggle('active');
  });
  ```

### 4.4 Accessibility Improvements
- Add skip-to-main link at top of body:
  ```html
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-to-main">Skip to main content</a>
  ```
- Add visible focus indicators to CSS:
  ```css
  a:focus, button:focus, input:focus {
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent-primary);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  ```
- Add ARIA labels to form inputs:
  ```html
  <input type="email" id="email" aria-label="Email address" required>
  ```
- Mark decorative emoji icons as `aria-hidden="true"`:
  ```html
  <div class="tool-icon" aria-hidden="true">📝</div>
  ```
- Verify heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3, no gaps)
- Test keyboard navigation (Tab key through entire site)
- Verify 4.5:1 contrast ratio on all text

### 4.5 Contact Form Validation
- Update contact form email input type:
  ```html
  <input type="email" id="email" required aria-label="Email address">
  ```
- Add JavaScript validation:
  ```javascript
  function validateEmail(email) {
    const regex = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/;
    return regex.test(email);
  }
  
  function validateContactForm() {
    const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
    const message = document.getElementById('message').value;
    
    if (!validateEmail(email)) {
      alert('Please enter a valid email');
      return false;
    }
    if (message.length < 10) {
      alert('Message must be at least 10 characters');
      return false;
    }
    return true;
  }
  ```
- Replace `alert()` with custom toast notification:
  ```javascript
  function showNotification(message, type = 'success') {
    const toast = document.createElement('div');
    toast.className = `toast toast-${type}`;
    toast.textContent = message;
    document.body.appendChild(toast);
    setTimeout(() => toast.remove(), 3000);
  }
  ```

### 4.6 Contact Form Backend (Optional)
- Use Formspree.io (no backend required):
  - Create free account
  - Update form `action="https://formspree.io/f/YOUR_ID"`
  - Set `method="POST"`
  - Emails will forward to your address
  - Alternative: Netlify Forms if hosting on Netlify

