## PHASE 5: MONETIZATION & ADVANCED SEO *(1 day)*

**Priority**: LOW - Implement after phases 1-4 show traffic growth

### 5.1 Activate Google AdSense
- Replace placeholder text with real AdSense code:
  - Get ad unit IDs from AdSense account
  - Update ad container divs with proper Google ad script
  - Test ads load correctly
  - Monitor CPM rates for tool pages vs blog pages

### 5.2 A/B Test Ad Placements
- Test variations:
  - Leaderboard above fold vs below fold
  - Rectangle on right sidebar vs inline
  - Multiple rectangles vs single
  - Ad frequency on blog vs tools
- Use Google Analytics events to correlate ad visibility with bounce rate

### 5.3 Add Affiliate Links
- Add disclosure: "This site contains affiliate links"
- Link to products mentioned:
  - Word Counter → Writing software (Amazon affiliate)
  - JSON Formatter → Developer tools
  - Password Generator → Cybersecurity courses
- Keep links natural (don't over-link)

### 5.4 Breadcrumb Schema
- Add to all pages after `<body>`:
  ```html
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://free-online-seo-tools.vercel.app/"},
      {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Tools", "item": "https://free-online-seo-tools.vercel.app/index.html"},
      {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Word Counter", "item": "https://free-online-seo-tools.vercel.app/tools/word-counter.html"}
    ]
  }
  </script>
  ```

### 5.5 FAQ Schema for Tools
- Add to each tool page:
  ```html
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is this tool free?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, completely free. No sign-up or account required."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is my data private?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Absolutely. This tool processes all data locally in your browser. We never store or transmit your data to our servers."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>
  ```

### 5.6 Internal Linking Strategy
- Update each tool page with "Related Tools" section:
  - URL Encoder ↔ Base64 Encoder (both encoding tools)
  - Markdown Converter → Blog post about markdown
  - JSON Formatter → API Integration Guide blog post
- Update blog posts with "Try the Tool" CTAs
- Create tools hub page listing all tools by category

